X_{i}(i=1,2..n)
P(X_{i}=m)=p(1-p)^{m-1}
\sum_{i=1}^{n}X_{i}
P(\sum_{i=1}^{n}X_{i}=n)=\binom{m-1}{n-1}p^{n}(1-p)^{m-n}
X_{1},X_{2},\ldots
p
P\left[X_{i}=m\right]=pq^{m-1}
m=1,2.\ldots
p+q=1
S_{n}:=X_{1}+\cdots+X_{n}
n
S_{n}
p
n
P\left\{ S_{n}=m\right\} =\binom{m-1}{n-1}p^{n}q^{m-n}
m=n,n+1,\ldots
n=1
S_{n+1}
m=n+1,n+2,\ldots
P\left[S_{n+1}=m\right]=\sum_{k=n}^{m-1}P\left[S_{n}=k\wedge X_{n+1}=m-k\right]=\sum_{k=n}^{m-1}P\left[S_{n}=k\right]\times P\left[X_{n+1}=m-k\right]
P\left[S_{n+1}=m\right]=p^{n+1}q^{m-n-1}\sum_{k=n}^{m-1}\binom{k-1}{n-1}
\sum_{k=n}^{m-1}\binom{k-1}{n-1}=\binom{m-1}{n}
m
\sum_{k=n}^{m}\binom{k-1}{n-1}=\sum_{k=n}^{m-1}\binom{k-1}{n-1}+\binom{m-1}{n-1}=\binom{m-1}{n}+\binom{m-1}{n-1}=\binom{m}{n}
